ARTinfoINDIA.COM’s Contemporary Portrait Art Exhibition 2015 and Creative Portrait Art Exhibition 2016 was successfully organized.

ARTinfoINDIA.COM invites you to participate in 'Faces & Portraits 2017' (A group art exhibition of faces & portraits only it can be Drawings / Paintings / Graphics / Photographs / Sculptures / Digital Art by Contemporary Modern / Abstract / Realistic artists to be held at Lokayata Art Gallery, Hauz Khas Village, New Delhi from 07-13 April, 2017

Warm Regards

Kishore Shanker

description.html:
______ Workshop Objective______
At the end of this course, participants will be able to:Understand the PRINCE2 principles, terminology and when qualified you will be able to act as an informed member of a project management team using the PRINCE2 methodology within a project environment supporting PRINCE2.

The PRINCE2 Practitioner qualification will teach you to apply PRINCE2 to the running and managing of a project within an environment supporting PRINCE2. Once qualified you will be able to apply and tune PRINCE2 to address the needs and problems of a specific project scenario. You will have a comprehensive knowledge of the relationships between the PRINCE2 principles, themes and processes and PRINCE2 products and will understand these elements.

___Prince2 Classroom Training Workshop Includes___
· AXELOS’s Accredited - Hardcopy of the courseware for Foundation and Practitioner.
· Sample Questions for Foundation.
· Sample Questions for Practitioner.
· Apply classroom concepts to project scenarios.
· Quiz, Case studies and Exercises.
 

Get Direct Inquiry From Here: http://trainings24x7.com/events/prince2-8/

description.text:
Lateral Thinking teaches one to solve problems through an indirect and creative approach, using reasoning that is not immediately obvious and involving ideas that may not be obtainable by using only traditional step-by-step logic.
Lateral thinking is regularly used by Fortune 500 companies.

By attending Lateral Thinking you will learn to:


Quick start creativity - apply structured thinking processes to facilitate personal and group idea generation.


Challenge current thinking by considering alternatives outside of the status quo and current thinking patterns.


Harvest and evaluate ideas generated in a creative session for practical implementation.


Generate unique solutions to difficult problems.


To find out more and to Register for the event follow the link.. http://genesiseventsindia.in/LT
Note : This is a paid workshop. Charges are Rs.15000/- per participant. The early bird rate if you register 1 week prior to the event is Rs.13500/- per participant.
